ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Average positive affect
Notes: Mean of positive affect items from active digital phenotyping/EMA/ESM from entire study period.

ElementDescription: Average negative affect
Notes: Mean of negative affect items from active digital phenotyping/EMA/ESM from entire study period.

ElementDescription: Number of times a strategy was attempted over the study period
How many emotion regulation strategies were used over the entire study period
Number of times they switched strategies because it was not working over the study period
Number of times they reported trying to stop using a strategy over the week
How long the emotion regulation strategy lasted on average
Notes: Average value in minutes; only displays if regulation is ongoing at time of survey

ElementDescription: Sum of times reappraisal was used
Sum of times suppression was used
Sum of times distraction was used
Sum of times situation modification was used
Average emotion regulation effort  across the week
Notes: Mean of emotion regulation effort from active digital phenotyping/EMA/ESM from entire study period.

ElementDescription: Average level of believing that they would be successful the next time they attempted a strategy
Notes: Mean of emotion regulation self-efficacy from active digital phenotyping/EMA/ESM from entire study period.

ElementDescription: Average emotional awareness over the course of the week
Notes: Mean of emotional awareness from active digital phenotyping/EMA/ESM from entire study period.

ElementDescription: Strategy: Avoidance
Timepoint/visit label
Strategy: Cognitive reappraisal
Strategy: Acceptance
Strategy: Problem Solving
Strategy: Thought suppression
Strategy: Rumination
